cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the application of quantum mechanics to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.AI sub-category. The use of Lie algebra theory in constructing quantum descriptions of everyday life situations also suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.SY (systems and control) sub-categories. The discussion of encoding thoughts in neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) sub-category. Finally, the mention of efficiency and generality gains suggests that it could belong to the cs.RO (robotics) sub-category.
